The paper focuses on developing a neural network for human pose estimation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses improvements in the network's architecture, which involves optimizing the matching of keypoints and their neighbors, and using a structure-aware loss function. These aspects suggest that the paper could also be relevant to the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper mentions the challenges of dealing with occlusions and complex multi-person scenarios, which could make it relevant to the sub-category cs.RO (Robotics).
